#. <section class="sutta" id="an11.21"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an11.21:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an11.21:0.2"
msgid "2. Anussativagga"
msgstr "2. Recollection"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an11.21:0.3"
msgid "21. Catutthasamādhisutta"
msgstr "21. Immersion (4th)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an11.21:1.1"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an11.21:1.2"
msgid ""
"“siyā nu kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā neva "
"pathaviyaṃ pathavisaññī assa, na āpasmiṃ āposaññī assa, na tejasmiṃ "
"tejosaññī assa, na vāyasmiṃ vāyosaññī assa, na ākāsānañcāyatane "
"ākāsānañcāyatanasaññī assa, na viññāṇañcāyatane viññāṇañcāyatanasaññī assa, "
"na ākiñcaññāyatane ākiñcaññāyatanasaññī assa, na nevasaññānāsaññāyatane "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasaññī assa, na idhaloke idhalokasaññī assa, na "
"paraloke paralokasaññī assa, yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ "
"pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tatrāpi na saññī assa; saññī ca pana assā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Could it be, reverends, that a mendicant might gain a state of immersion "
"like this? They wouldn’t perceive earth in earth, water in water, fire in "
"fire, or air in air. And they wouldn’t perceive the dimension of infinite "
"space in the dimension of infinite space, the dimension of infinite "
"consciousness in the dimension of infinite consciousness, the dimension of "
"nothingness in the dimension of nothingness, or the dimension of neither "
"perception nor non-perception in the dimension of neither perception nor non-"
"perception. They wouldn’t perceive this world in this world, or the other "
"world in the other world. And they wouldn’t perceive what is seen, heard, "
"thought, cognized, attained, sought, or explored by the mind. And yet they "
"would still perceive.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an11.21:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Dūratopi kho mayaṃ, āvuso, āgaccheyyāma āyasmato sāriputtassa santike "
"etassa bhāsitassa atthamaññātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend, we would travel a long way to learn the meaning of this statement "
"in the presence of Venerable Sāriputta."

msgctxt "an11.21:2.2"
msgid "Sādhu vatāyasmantaṃyeva sāriputtaṃ paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho."
msgstr "May Venerable Sāriputta himself please clarify the meaning of this."

msgctxt "an11.21:2.3"
msgid "Āyasmato sāriputtassa sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr "The mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.358"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an11.21:3.1"
msgid "“Tenahāvuso, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha; bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Then listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "an11.21:3.2"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, friend,” they replied."

msgctxt "an11.21:3.3"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an11.21:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Siyā, āvuso, bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā neva pathaviyaṃ "
"pathavisaññī assa … pe … yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ "
"pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tatrāpi na saññī assa; saññī ca pana assā”ti."
msgstr "“A mendicant could gain such a state of immersion.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an11.21:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ panāvuso, siyā bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā neva "
"pathaviyaṃ pathavisaññī assa … pe … yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ "
"pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tatrāpi na saññī assa; saññī ca pana "
"assā”ti?"
msgstr "“But how could this be?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an11.21:6.1"
msgid "“Idha, āvuso, bhikkhu evaṃsaññī hoti:"
msgstr "“It’s when a mendicant perceives:"

msgctxt "an11.21:6.2"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ, yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho "
"sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful; this is sublime—that is, the stilling of all activities, "
"the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, "
"cessation, extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "an11.21:6.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, āvuso, siyā bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā neva "
"pathaviyaṃ pathavisaññī assa, na āpasmiṃ āposaññī assa, na tejasmiṃ "
"tejosaññī assa, na vāyasmiṃ vāyosaññī assa, na ākāsānañcāyatane "
"ākāsānañcāyatanasaññī assa, na viññāṇañcāyatane viññāṇañcāyatanasaññī assa, "
"na ākiñcaññāyatane ākiñcaññāyatanasaññī assa, na nevasaññānāsaññāyatane "
"nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasaññī assa, na idhaloke idhalokasaññī assa, na "
"paraloke paralokasaññī assa, yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ "
"pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tatrāpi na saññī assa; saññī ca pana assā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant might gain a state of immersion like this. They "
"wouldn’t perceive earth in earth, water in water, fire in fire, or air in "
"air. And they wouldn’t perceive the dimension of infinite space in the "
"dimension of infinite space, the dimension of infinite consciousness in the "
"dimension of infinite consciousness, the dimension of nothingness in the "
"dimension of nothingness, or the dimension of neither perception nor non-"
"perception in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. They "
"wouldn’t perceive this world in this world, or the other world in the other "
"world. And they wouldn’t perceive what is seen, heard, thought, cognized, "
"attained, sought, or explored by the mind. And yet they would still "
"perceive.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an11.21:6.4"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an11.21:6.5"
msgid "Anussativaggo dutiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
